cards.name: Karn Liberated
cards.oracle_text:
+4: Target player exiles a card from their hand.
−3: Exile target permanent.
−14: Restart the game, leaving in exile all non-Aura permanent cards exiled with Karn Liberated. Then put those cards onto the battlefield under your control.

cards.name: A-Elderleaf Mentor
cards.oracle_text: When Elderleaf Mentor enters the battlefield, create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token.

cards.name: Davriel, Soul Broker
cards.oracle_text:
+1: Until your next turn, whenever an opponent attacks you and/or planeswalkers you control, they discard a card. If they can't, they sacrifice an attacking creature.
−2: Accept one of Davriel's offers, then accept one of Davriel's conditions.
−3: Target creature an opponent controls perpetually gets -3/-3.

cards.name: Velomachus Lorehold
cards.oracle_text:
Flying, vigilance, haste
Whenever Velomachus Lorehold attacks, look at the top seven cards of your library. You may cast an instant or sorcery spell with mana value less than or equal to Velomachus Lorehold's power from among them without paying its mana cost. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.

cards.name: Sea Drake
cards.oracle_text:
Flying
When Sea Drake enters the battlefield, return two target lands you control to their owner's hand.

cards.name: Cleaver Riot
cards.oracle_text: Creatures you control gain double strike until end of turn. (They deal both first-strike and regular combat damage.)
cards.flavor_text: Measure once, cut twice.

cards.name: Alaborn Grenadier
cards.oracle_text: Vigilance
cards.flavor_text:
"Ever proud, ever vigilant."
—Grenadier motto

cards.name: Elf Replica
cards.oracle_text: {1}{G}, Sacrifice Elf Replica: Destroy target enchantment.
cards.flavor_text: It hunts with unnerving ferocity.

cards.name: Stoneskin
cards.oracle_text:
Flash
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +0/+10.
cards.set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
cards.flavor_text: "Ooh, nice shot! I almost felt that one."

cards.name: Minamo Sightbender
cards.oracle_text: {X}, {T}: Target creature with power X or less can't be blocked this turn.
cards.flavor_text: Woven from threads of the spirit world, the mistcloak rendered its wearer invisible, but quickly fell to tatters.

cards.name: Barging Sergeant
cards.oracle_text:
Haste
Mentor (Whenever this creature attacks, put a +1/+1 counter on target attacking creature with lesser power.)
cards.flavor_text: "Don't stop till your horns come out their back."

cards.name: Fabled Passage
cards.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Fabled Passage: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle. Then if you control four or more lands, untap that land.

cards.name: Decomposition
cards.oracle_text:
Enchant black creature
Enchanted creature has "Cumulative upkeep—Pay 1 life." (At the beginning of its controller's upkeep, that player puts an age counter on it, then sacrifices it unless they pay its upkeep cost for each age counter on it.)
When enchanted creature dies, its controller loses 2 life.

cards.name: Ancestral Tribute
cards.oracle_text:
You gain 2 life for each card in your graveyard.
Flashback {9}{W}{W}{W} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

cards.name: Heartstone
cards.oracle_text: Activated abilities of creatures cost {1} less to activate. This effect can't reduce the mana in that cost to less than one mana.
cards.flavor_text:
"Finding a true heartstone is even harder than finding a true heart."
—Hanna, *Weatherlight* navigator

cards.name: Vigilante Justice
cards.oracle_text: Whenever a Human enters the battlefield under your control, Vigilante Justice deals 1 damage to any target.
cards.flavor_text: It begins as a whisper and ends with the red roar of fire.

cards.name: Morale
cards.oracle_text: Attacking creatures get +1/+1 until end of turn.
cards.flavor_text: "After Lacjsi's speech, the Knights grew determined to crush their ancient enemies clan by clan." —Tivadar of Thorn, *History of the Goblin Wars*

cards.name: Hanweir Garrison
cards.oracle_text:
Whenever Hanweir Garrison attacks, create two 1/1 red Human creature tokens that are tapped and attacking.
(Melds with Hanweir Battlements.)
cards.flavor_text: "We're ready for anything!"

cards.name: Rousing of Souls
cards.oracle_text: Parley — Each player reveals the top card of their library. For each nonland card revealed this way, you create a 1/1 white Spirit creature token with flying. Then each player draws a card.
cards.flavor_text: "We remember. We rise."

cards.name: Roc of Kher Ridges
cards.oracle_text: Flying

cards.name: Morphic Tide
cards.oracle_text: When you encounter Morphic Tide, each player shuffles all permanents they own into their library, then reveals that many cards from the top of their library. Each player puts all artifact, creature, land, and planeswalker cards revealed this way onto the battlefield, then does the same for enchantment cards, then puts all cards revealed this way that weren't put onto the battlefield on the bottom of their library in any order. (Then planeswalk away from this phenomenon.)

cards.name: Mind Slash
cards.oracle_text: {B}, Sacrifice a creature: Target opponent reveals their hand. You choose a card from it. That player discards that card. Activate only as a sorcery.
cards.flavor_text: "I can't think with all that screaming."

cards.name: Merfolk Seer
cards.oracle_text: When Merfolk Seer dies, you may pay {1}{U}. If you do, draw a card.
cards.flavor_text:
The sea leaves no room for tears.
—Zhalfirin adage

cards.name: Liliana of the Dark Realms
cards.oracle_text:
+1: Search your library for a Swamp card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
−3: Target creature gets +X/+X or -X/-X until end of turn, where X is the number of Swamps you control.
−6: You get an emblem with "Swamps you control have '{T}: Add {B}{B}{B}{B}.'"

all_parts.name: Liliana of the Dark Realms Emblem

cards.name: Blood Tithe
cards.oracle_text: Each opponent loses 3 life. You gain life equal to the life lost this way.
cards.flavor_text: The Crimson Throne may be empty, but its coffers are full.

cards.name: Siege Behemoth
cards.oracle_text:
Hexproof
As long as Siege Behemoth is attacking, for each creature you control, you may have that creature assign its combat damage as though it weren't blocked.
cards.flavor_text:
"Hold the line, hold the li—"
—General Srok, last words

cards.name: Ceta Sanctuary
cards.oracle_text: At the beginning of your upkeep, if you control a red or green permanent, draw a card, then discard a card. If you control a red permanent and a green permanent, instead draw two cards, then discard a card.

cards.name: Vile Requiem
cards.oracle_text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, you may put a verse counter on Vile Requiem.
{1}{B}, Sacrifice Vile Requiem: Destroy up to X target nonblack creatures, where X is the number of verse counters on Vile Requiem. They can't be regenerated.

cards.name: Spectral Sliver
cards.oracle_text: All Sliver creatures have "{2}: This creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn."
cards.flavor_text:
"Sure, I've seen agents of the Cabal here and there. Well, not here, and certainly not in any of the sliver labs. Oh dear, I've said too much."
—Apprentice researcher

cards.name: Starlit Mantle
cards.oracle_text:
Flash
Enchant creature you control
When Starlit Mantle enters the battlefield, enchanted creature gains hexproof until end of turn. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities your opponents control.)
Enchanted creature gets +1/+1.

cards.name: Deadbridge Goliath
cards.oracle_text: Scavenge {4}{G}{G} ({4}{G}{G}, Exile this card from your graveyard: Put a number of +1/+1 counters equal to this card's power on target creature. Scavenge only as a sorcery.)
cards.flavor_text: Some Golgari insects live for centuries-and they never stop growing.

cards.name: Suffocation
cards.oracle_text:
Cast this spell only if you were dealt damage this turn by a red instant or sorcery spell.
Suffocation deals 4 damage to the controller of the last red instant or sorcery spell that dealt damage to you this turn.
Draw a card at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.

cards.name: Bilious Skulldweller
cards.oracle_text:
Deathtouch
Toxic 1 (Players dealt combat damage by this creature also get a poison counter.)
cards.flavor_text:
"Watch your footing around here. Anything you might step on probably has teeth."
—Kara Vrist, resistance spymaster

cards.name: Dungeon Descent
cards.oracle_text:
Dungeon Descent enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {C}.
{4}, {T}, Tap an untapped legendary creature you control: Venture into the dungeon. Activate only as a sorcery. (Enter the first room or advance to the next room.)

cards.name: Haazda Snare Squad
cards.oracle_text: Whenever Haazda Snare Squad attacks, you may pay {W}. If you do, tap target creature an opponent controls.
cards.flavor_text: They've been probation officers, army grunts, bounty hunters—anything to make their district safer.

cards.name: Flash
cards.oracle_text: You may put a creature card from your hand onto the battlefield. If you do, sacrifice it unless you pay its mana cost reduced by up to {2}.

cards.name: Bojuka Brigand
cards.oracle_text:
Bojuka Brigand can't block.
Whenever Bojuka Brigand or another Ally enters the battlefield under your control, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Bojuka Brigand.
cards.flavor_text: "I don't do tactics. I don't do guard duty. I do damage. Take it or leave it."

cards.name: Telling Time
cards.oracle_text: Look at the top three cards of your library. Put one of those cards into your hand, one on top of your library, and one on the bottom of your library.
cards.flavor_text: Mastery is achieved when "telling time" becomes "telling time what to do."

cards.name: Steamflogger Boss
cards.oracle_text:
Other Riggers you control get +1/+0 and have haste.
If a Rigger you control would assemble a Contraption, it assembles two Contraptions instead.
cards.flavor_text:
"Don't quit now, we're almost done.
Then we'll build another one!"

cards.name: Hidden Path
cards.oracle_text: Green creatures have forestwalk. (They can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
cards.flavor_text:
"Where moments before we were lost beyond hope, the strange, floating lights showed us the way and restored our morale."
—Vervamon the Elder

cards.name: Manaweft Sliver
cards.oracle_text: Sliver creatures you control have "{T}: Add one mana of any color."
cards.flavor_text:
"I see in their interconnectedness a strange embodiment of the natural order."
—Dionus, elvish archdruid

cards.name: Beast Within
cards.oracle_text: Destroy target permanent. Its controller creates a 3/3 green Beast creature token.

cards.name: Blasphemous Act
cards.oracle_text:
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each creature on the battlefield.
Blasphemous Act deals 13 damage to each creature.

cards.name: Decree of Pain
cards.oracle_text:
Destroy all creatures. They can't be regenerated. Draw a card for each creature destroyed this way.
Cycling {3}{B}{B} ({3}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
When you cycle Decree of Pain, all creatures get -2/-2 until end of turn.

cards.name: Elmar, Ulvenwald Informant
cards.oracle_text:
Haste
Whenever you cast your second spell each turn, untap target creature, then investigate. (Create a colorless Clue artifact token with "{2}, Sacrifice this artifact: Draw a card.")
Friends forever (You can have two commanders if both have friends forever.)

cards.name: Keldon Strike Team
cards.oracle_text:
Kicker {1}{W} (You may pay an additional {1}{W} as you cast this spell.)
When Keldon Strike Team enters the battlefield, if it was kicked, create two 1/1 white Soldier creature tokens.
As long as Keldon Strike Team entered the battlefield this turn, creatures you control have haste.

cards.oracle_text:
+1: You gain 2 life. Add {U}, {R}, or {W}. Spend this mana only to cast a noncreature spell.
−2: Draw a card, then you may discard a card. When you discard a nonland card this way, Narset of the Ancient Way deals damage equal to that card's mana value to target creature or planeswalker.
−6: You get an emblem with "Whenever you cast a noncreature spell, this emblem deals 2 damage to any target."

Ertai, the Corrupted
